    "headerDoc": "STEP 897 + 898 + 899 + 894 — Additive / Diophantine Problems\n  =============================================================\n\n  Four classical additive / Diophantine conjectures:\n    (a) Goldbach:       every even n ≥ 4 is sum of two primes\n    (b) Lemoine:        every odd n ≥ 7 is p + 2q with p,q prime\n    (c) Fermat-Catalan: finitely many (a^m + b^n = c^k, 1/m+1/n+1/k < 1)\n    (d) Sum of 3 cubes: which n are a³ + b³ + c³ (a,b,c ∈ ℤ)\n\n  Each is stated as Prop + axiom; small explicit cases verified."
